Selex Sistemi Integrati SpA, a unit
of  Finmeccanica SpA , may post a 150 million-euro ($197 million)
loss for 2011,  Il Messaggero  reported, citing a draft of the
accounts that will be approved Feb. 27.  The division develops radar systems and other military and
civil security measures.  To contact the reporter on this story:
